The Judge knew something of wines, and could tell all the famous old Madeiras from each other, âEclipse,â âJuno,â the almost fabulously scarce and precious âWhite-top,â and the rest.
He struck the nativity of the Mediterranean Madeira before it had fairly moistened his lip.
âA sound wine, Colonel, and I should think of a genuine vintage.
