â And the old green de-lame, with the young curves under it to make it sit well, moved off as pleased apparently as if it had been silk velvet with thousand-dollar laces over it.
âOh, now, Miss Green!
do you think it's safe to put that cold stuff into your stomick?
â said the Widow Leech to a young married lady, who, finding the air rather warm, thought a little ice would cool her down very nicely.
âIt's jest like eatin' snowballs.
You don't look very rugged; and I should be dreadful afeard, if I was you.
â
âCarrie,â said old Dr. Kittredge, who had overheard this,--âhow well you're looking this evening!
