â the Doctor said, with that shade of curiosity in his tone which a metaphysician would probably say is an index of a certain tendency to belief in the superstition to which the question refers.
âI ca'n' jestly tell y' what it was, Doctor,â the old woman answered, as if bewildered and trying to clear up her recollections; âbut it was somethin' fearful, with a great noise 'n' a great cryin' o' people,--like the Las' Day, Doctor!
The Lord have mercy on my poor chil', 'n' take care of her, if anything happens!
