Poor Sophy, only the third generation from cannibalism, was, not unnaturally, somewhat confused in her theological notions.
Some of the Second-Advent preachers had been about, and circulated their predictions among the kitchen--population of Rockland.
This was the way in which it happened that she mingled her fears in such a strange manner with their doctrines.
The Doctor answered solemnly, that of the day and hour we knew not, but it became us to be always ready.
