â
Dick lay perfectly still, feeling that he was crippled and helpless, thinking all the time with the Yankee half of his mind what to do about it.
He saw Mr. Bernard lift his head and look around him.
He would get his senses again in a few minutes, very probably, and then he, Mr. Richard Venner, would be done for.
